<a href="/updates?edit=nm0006890/details&ref_=nm_pdt_edt" > Edit
</a>        </span>
    <h2>Personal Details</h2>
        <div id="details-other-works" class="see-more inline canwrap">
                <h4 class="inline">Other Works:</h4>
He acted in Thomas Otway's play, "Venice Preserv'd," at the Lyric Theatre in Hammersmith, London, England with John Gielgud, Eileen Herlie, Pamela Brown, and Eric Porter in the cast. Peter Brook was director.                    <span class="see-more inline">
                        <a href="/name/nm0006890/otherworks?ref_=nm_pdt_wrk_sm" >See more</a> 
                    </span>
                    &raquo;
        </div>
    
    
    
            <hr/>
        <div id="details-height" class="see-more inline canwrap">
            <h4 class="inline">Height:</h4>
6'&nbsp;1"&nbsp;(1.85&nbsp;m)        </div>
            </div> 
            <div class="article">
        <span class="rightcornerlink">
<a href="/updates?edit=nm0006890/fun-facts&ref_=nm_dyk_edt" > Edit
</a>        </span>
    <h2>Did You Know?</h2>
        <div id="dyk-personal-quote" class="see-more inline canwrap">
                <h4 class="inline">Personal Quote:</h4>
[upon being notified of his Oscar win, having not been present at the actual ceremony, 1967] Oh, I suppose my wife and I will open a bottle of champagne with another couple.                    <span class="see-more inline">
                        <a href="/name/nm0006890/bio?ref_=nm_dyk_qt_sm#quotes" >See more</a> 
                    </span>
                    &raquo;
        </div>
            <hr/>
        <div id="dyk-trivia" class="see-more inline canwrap">
                <h4 class="inline">Trivia:</h4>
He was nominated for 1997 <a href="/name/nm0000059/?ref_=nm_dyk_trv1">Laurence Olivier</a> Theatre Award for Best Actor in a Play of 1996 for his performance in John Gabriel Borkman.                    <span class="see-more inline">
                        <a href="/name/nm0006890/bio?ref_=nm_dyk_trv_sm#trivia" >See more</a>
                    </span>
                    &raquo;
        </div>
    
    
            <hr/>
        <div id="dyk-star-sign" class="see-more inline canwrap">
            <h4 class="inline">Star Sign:</h4>
            <a href="/starsign/aquarius?ref_=nm_dyk_sign" >Aquarius</a>
        </div>
            </div> 
